text: Federal prosecutors have charged 4 former employees of Washington Federal Bank for Savings for allegedly embezzling $29 million, as part of an ongoing criminal investigation of the Bridgeport bank's 2017 failure https://t.co/zEpD1dLBfu

name: chicagotribune
text:
RT @MarySchmich: The Democrats’ convention
Was a boring show online
They propped up Sleepy Biden
While they did their dance and whine
Their vision of our country
It was very, let’s say, black
But I am here with light and cheer:
Let’s take our nation back!
Today's column.

 https://t.co/7pBak2WYKC

name: chicagotribune
text:
RT @EricZorn: Lefties have one job in the next two months — to work to vote Trump out of office. If they fail in that, in part by feeding the narrative of chaos and lawlessness peddled by the right, their other efforts will have been in vain.

https://t.co/YUsWDPTVYv

text: Chicago's historic Graceland Cemetery has been closed since a powerful storm tore through the area earlier this month, leaving loved ones of those buried there unable to visit for the foreseeable future https://t.co/PfWzBYNqig
